-- Bank of China to open regional CEE centre in Hungary 
-- 
-- Mon Oct 27, 2014 11:39AM EDT
-- None



BUDAPEST, Oct 27 (Reuters) - The Bank of China <601988.SS> <3988.HK> will open its regional central eastern European centre in Budapest this year, the Hungarian Ministry of Foreign Affairs said on Monday.

Hungarian Foreign Minister Peter Szijjarto is currently on a visit to China. The Bank of China has already co-operated with Hungarian state-owned Eximbank in financing investment projects in Hungary in the past. The Foreign Ministry did not provide any further details.